cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the analysis of coverage probability and interference, which are key concepts in information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on modeling and analyzing wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The use of stochastic geometry to model and analyze wireless networks can be seen as a control problem, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with multi-cluster wireless networks, which can be seen as a multiagent system where each transmitter and receiver is an agent. 
- cs.PF (Probability): The paper uses probability theory to derive the link distance distribution and the Laplace transform of the interference, which falls under the scope of probability.
